## 📖 Overview

RAG College Assistant ingests 280+ pages of institutional documentation and lets users query it in natural language instead of digging through PDFs and handbooks. The core engineering challenge was retrieval **precision** — returning only the passages the model actually needs, so responses stay accurate and cheap to generate.

## ✨ Key Features

- 🔀 **Hybrid retrieval** — combines semantic search (OpenAI embeddings) with keyword-based BM25 search, so it catches both conceptual questions and exact-term lookups
- 🎯 **Cross-encoder reranking** — a second-pass reranker filters the hybrid results down to only the most relevant chunks before they reach the LLM
- 💰 **90%+ token reduction** — precise retrieval means the model only sees what it needs, cutting inference cost dramatically compared to naive "dump everything into context" RAG
- ⚡ **Gemini 2.0 Flash** as the generation backend for fast, low-latency responses
- 🖥️ **Next.js frontend** for a clean chat interface

## 🏗️ Architecture

```
User Query
   │
   ▼
┌─────────────────────────────┐
│   Hybrid Retrieval Layer    │
│  ┌───────────┐ ┌──────────┐ │
│  │ Semantic  │ │  BM25    │ │
│  │ (OpenAI   │ │ (keyword)│ │
│  │ embeddings│ │          │ │
│  │ + Pinecone│ │          │ │
│  └─────┬─────┘ └────┬─────┘ │
│        └──────┬─────┘       │
│         Cross-Encoder       │
│           Reranker          │
└──────────────┬──────────────┘
               ▼
        Gemini 2.0 Flash
               ▼
          Final Answer
```

## 🧰 Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|---|---|
| Backend API | FastAPI (Python) |
| Vector Store | Pinecone |
| Embeddings | OpenAI Embeddings |
| Search | Hybrid: semantic + BM25 |
| Reranking | Cross-encoder model |
| LLM | Gemini 2.0 Flash |
| Frontend | Next.js |

## 🚀 Getting Started

```bash
# clone
git clone https://github.com/hackerstudent29/ragmsajce.git
cd ragmsajce

# backend
cd backend
pip install -r requirements.txt
uvicorn main:app --reload

# frontend
cd ../frontend
npm install
npm run dev
```

Create a `.env` file with your API keys:
```
OPENAI_API_KEY=your_key
PINECONE_API_KEY=your_key
GEMINI_API_KEY=your_key
```

